{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":722,"text":"\"Why?\""},{"time":2231,"text":"\"Why?\" is a question"},{"time":3689,"text":"that parents ask me all the time."},{"time":6325,"text":"\"Why did my child develop autism?\""},{"time":9172,"text":"As a pediatrician, as a geneticist, as a researcher,"},{"time":13626,"text":"we try and address that question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16069,"text":"But autism is not a single condition."},{"time":18018,"text":"It's actually a spectrum of disorders,"},{"time":20733,"text":"a spectrum that ranges, for instance,"},{"time":23267,"text":"from Justin, a 13-year-old boy"},{"time":25940,"text":"who's not verbal, who can't speak,"},{"time":29163,"text":"who communicates by using an iPad"},{"time":31125,"text":"to touch pictures to communicate"},{"time":33023,"text":"his thoughts and his concerns,"},{"time":35174,"text":"a little boy who, when he gets upset,"},{"time":37585,"text":"will start rocking,"},{"time":39233,"text":"and eventually, when he's disturbed enough,"},{"time":40830,"text":"will bang his head to the point"},{"time":42433,"text":"that he can actually cut it open and require stitches."},{"time":46275,"text":"That same diagnosis of autism, though,"},{"time":48890,"text":"also applies to Gabriel,"},{"time":50812,"text":"another 13-year-old boy"},{"time":52779,"text":"who has quite a different set of challenges."},{"time":55474,"text":"He's actually quite remarkably gifted in mathematics."},{"time":58588,"text":"He can multiple three numbers by three numbers"},{"time":60609,"text":"in his head with ease,"},{"time":62396,"text":"yet when it comes to trying to have a conversation,"},{"time":66154,"text":"he has great difficulty."},{"time":68215,"text":"He doesn't make eye contact."},{"time":70274,"text":"He has difficulty starting a conversation,"},{"time":72397,"text":"feels awkward,"},{"time":74132,"text":"and when he gets nervous,"},{"time":75950,"text":"he actually shuts down."},{"time":77675,"text":"Yet both of these boys"},{"time":79157,"text":"have the same diagnosis of\nautism spectrum disorder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83341,"text":"One of the things that concerns us"},{"time":85769,"text":"is whether or not there really is"},{"time":87366,"text":"an epidemic of autism."},{"time":89339,"text":"These days, one in 88 children"},{"time":91819,"text":"will be diagnosed with autism,"},{"time":93861,"text":"and the question is,"},{"time":95334,"text":"why does this graph look this way?"},{"time":97337,"text":"Has that number been increasing"},{"time":99304,"text":"dramatically over time?"},{"time":101238,"text":"Or is it because we have now started labeling"},{"time":105769,"text":"individuals with autism,"},{"time":107331,"text":"simply giving them a diagnosis"},{"time":109579,"text":"when they were still present there before"},{"time":112132,"text":"yet simply didn't have that label?"},{"time":114525,"text":"And in fact, in the late 1980s, the early 1990s,"},{"time":118516,"text":"legislation was passed"},{"time":119926,"text":"that actually provided individuals with autism"},{"time":122565,"text":"with resources, with access to educational materials"},{"time":126291,"text":"that would help them."},{"time":128063,"text":"With that increased awareness, more parents,"},{"time":131551,"text":"more pediatricians, more educators"},{"time":134297,"text":"learned to recognize the features of autism."},{"time":137552,"text":"As a result of that, more individuals were diagnosed"},{"time":141562,"text":"and got access to the resources they needed."},{"time":144750,"text":"In addition, we've changed our definition over time,"},{"time":148182,"text":"so in fact we've widened the definition of autism,"},{"time":151320,"text":"and that accounts for some of"},{"time":152440,"text":"the increased prevalence that we see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155455,"text":"The next question everyone wonders is,"},{"time":158115,"text":"what caused autism?"},{"time":159891,"text":"And a common misconception"},{"time":162786,"text":"is that vaccines cause autism."},{"time":165570,"text":"But let me be very clear:"},{"time":168621,"text":"Vaccines do not cause autism."},{"time":173108,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":179812,"text":"In fact, the original research study"},{"time":181935,"text":"that suggested that was the case"},{"time":183934,"text":"was completely fraudulent."},{"time":186809,"text":"It was actually retracted from the journal Lancet,"},{"time":189985,"text":"in which it was published,"},{"time":191577,"text":"and that author, a physician,"},{"time":193467,"text":"had his medical license taken away from him."},{"time":196721,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":200675,"text":"The Institute of Medicine,"},{"time":202257,"text":"The Centers for Disease Control,"},{"time":203820,"text":"have repeatedly investigated this"},{"time":206164,"text":"and there is no credible evidence"},{"time":209771,"text":"that vaccines cause autism."},{"time":212456,"text":"Furthermore,"},{"time":214093,"text":"one of the ingredients in vaccines,"},{"time":216562,"text":"something called thimerosal,"},{"time":218614,"text":"was thought to be what the cause of autism was."},{"time":221930,"text":"That was actually removed from vaccines"},{"time":224193,"text":"in the year 1992,"},{"time":225918,"text":"and you can see that it really did not have an effect"},{"time":228962,"text":"in what happened with the prevalence of autism."},{"time":231601,"text":"So again, there is no evidence"},{"time":233334,"text":"that this is the answer."},{"time":235416,"text":"So the question remains, what does cause autism?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":239559,"text":"In fact, there's probably not one single answer."},{"time":242390,"text":"Just as autism is a spectrum,"},{"time":244147,"text":"there's a spectrum of etiologies,"},{"time":246337,"text":"a spectrum of causes."},{"time":247989,"text":"Based on epidemiological data,"},{"time":249980,"text":"we know that one of the causes,"},{"time":251773,"text":"or one of the associations, I should say,"},{"time":253930,"text":"is advanced paternal age,"},{"time":256214,"text":"that is, increasing age of the father"},{"time":258151,"text":"at the time of conception."},{"time":260330,"text":"In addition, another vulnerable"},{"time":262474,"text":"and critical period in terms of development"},{"time":265104,"text":"is when the mother is pregnant."},{"time":267010,"text":"During that period, while\nthe fetal brain is developing,"},{"time":270000,"text":"we know that exposure to certain agents"},{"time":271942,"text":"can actually increase the risk of autism."},{"time":275027,"text":"In particular, there's a medication, valproic acid,"},{"time":277962,"text":"which mothers with epilepsy sometimes take,"},{"time":280548,"text":"we know can increase that risk of autism."},{"time":284220,"text":"In addition, there can be some infectious agents"},{"time":286519,"text":"that can also cause autism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289419,"text":"And one of the things I'm going to spend"},{"time":290999,"text":"a lot of time focusing on"},{"time":293060,"text":"are the genes that can cause autism."},{"time":295621,"text":"I'm focusing on this not because genes"},{"time":298077,"text":"are the only cause of autism,"},{"time":300221,"text":"but it's a cause of autism"},{"time":301790,"text":"that we can readily define"},{"time":303667,"text":"and be able to better understand the biology"},{"time":306460,"text":"and understand better how the brain works"},{"time":308729,"text":"so that we can come up with strategies"},{"time":310714,"text":"to be able to intervene."},{"time":313044,"text":"One of the genetic factors that we don't understand,"},{"time":315990,"text":"however, is the difference that we see"},{"time":319138,"text":"in terms of males and females."},{"time":321044,"text":"Males are affected four to one compared to females"},{"time":324049,"text":"with autism,"},{"time":325151,"text":"and we really don't understand what that cause is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329142,"text":"One of the ways that we can understand"},{"time":330860,"text":"that genetics is a factor"},{"time":332723,"text":"is by looking at something called"},{"time":334060,"text":"the concordance rate."},{"time":335950,"text":"In other words, if one sibling has autism,"},{"time":339138,"text":"what's the probability"},{"time":340625,"text":"that another sibling in that family will have autism?"},{"time":343629,"text":"And we can look in particular"},{"time":345194,"text":"at three types of siblings:"},{"time":347362,"text":"identical twins,"},{"time":349233,"text":"twins that actually share 100 percent"},{"time":351452,"text":"of their genetic information"},{"time":353054,"text":"and shared the same intrauterine environment,"},{"time":356230,"text":"versus fraternal twins,"},{"time":358475,"text":"twins that actually share 50 percent"},{"time":360464,"text":"of their genetic information,"},{"time":362491,"text":"versus regular siblings,"},{"time":363707,"text":"brother-sister, sister-sister,"},{"time":365576,"text":"also sharing 50 percent of their genetic information,"},{"time":368444,"text":"yet not sharing the same intrauterine environment."},{"time":371523,"text":"And when you look at those concordance ratios,"},{"time":373823,"text":"one of the striking things that you will see"},{"time":375880,"text":"is that in identical twins,"},{"time":378000,"text":"that concordance rate is 77 percent."},{"time":381353,"text":"Remarkably, though,"},{"time":382457,"text":"it's not 100 percent."},{"time":384605,"text":"It is not that genes account\nfor all of the risk for autism,"},{"time":388608,"text":"but yet they account for a lot of that risk,"},{"time":390849,"text":"because when you look at fraternal twins,"},{"time":393162,"text":"that concordance rate is only 31 percent."},{"time":396238,"text":"On the other hand, there is a difference"},{"time":398149,"text":"between those fraternal twins and the siblings,"},{"time":401092,"text":"suggesting that there are common exposures"},{"time":403756,"text":"for those fraternal twins"},{"time":405179,"text":"that may not be shared as commonly"},{"time":407296,"text":"with siblings alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409470,"text":"So this provides some of the data"},{"time":411156,"text":"that autism is genetic."},{"time":412778,"text":"Well, how genetic is it?"},{"time":414742,"text":"When we compare it to other conditions"},{"time":416585,"text":"that we're familiar with,"},{"time":418197,"text":"things like cancer, heart disease, diabetes,"},{"time":422077,"text":"in fact, genetics plays a much larger role in autism"},{"time":426030,"text":"than it does in any of these other conditions."},{"time":428470,"text":"But with this, that doesn't\ntell us what the genes are."},{"time":431812,"text":"It doesn't even tell us in any one child,"},{"time":434479,"text":"is it one gene"},{"time":436140,"text":"or potentially a combination of genes?"},{"time":438396,"text":"And so in fact, in some individuals with autism,"},{"time":441950,"text":"it is genetic!"},{"time":444464,"text":"That is, that it is one single,"},{"time":446694,"text":"powerful, deterministic gene"},{"time":448866,"text":"that causes the autism."},{"time":450713,"text":"However, in other individuals,"},{"time":452507,"text":"it's genetic, that is,"},{"time":454213,"text":"that it's actually a combination of genes"},{"time":457333,"text":"in part with the developmental process"},{"time":460128,"text":"that ultimately determines that risk for autism."},{"time":463508,"text":"We don't know in any one person, necessarily,"},{"time":466378,"text":"which of those two answers it is"},{"time":468471,"text":"until we start digging deeper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470512,"text":"So the question becomes,"},{"time":471799,"text":"how can we start to identify"},{"time":474040,"text":"what exactly those genes are."},{"time":475912,"text":"And let me pose something"},{"time":477021,"text":"that might not be intuitive."},{"time":479211,"text":"In certain individuals,"},{"time":481570,"text":"they can have autism"},{"time":483294,"text":"for a reason that is genetic"},{"time":485747,"text":"but yet not because of autism running in the family."},{"time":489311,"text":"And the reason is because in certain individuals,"},{"time":491690,"text":"they can actually have genetic changes or mutations"},{"time":494751,"text":"that are not passed down from the mother"},{"time":497794,"text":"or from the father,"},{"time":499281,"text":"but actually start brand new in them,"},{"time":502014,"text":"mutations that are present"},{"time":503601,"text":"in the egg or the sperm"},{"time":505004,"text":"at the time of conception"},{"time":506617,"text":"but have not been passed down"},{"time":508359,"text":"generation through generation within the family."},{"time":511365,"text":"And we can actually use that strategy"},{"time":513546,"text":"to now understand and to identify"},{"time":515880,"text":"those genes causing autism in those individuals."},{"time":518980,"text":"So in fact, at the Simons Foundation,"},{"time":520990,"text":"we took 2,600 individuals"},{"time":523716,"text":"that had no family history of autism,"},{"time":526427,"text":"and we took that child and their mother and father"},{"time":529597,"text":"and used them to try and understand"},{"time":532068,"text":"what were those genes"},{"time":533687,"text":"causing autism in those cases?"},{"time":536005,"text":"To do that, we actually had to comprehensively"},{"time":539072,"text":"be able to look at all that genetic information"},{"time":541802,"text":"and determine what those differences were"},{"time":543984,"text":"between the mother, the father and the child."},{"time":547685,"text":"In doing so, I apologize,"},{"time":549639,"text":"I'm going to use an outdated analogy"},{"time":551523,"text":"of encyclopedias rather than Wikipedia,"},{"time":554181,"text":"but I'm going to do so to try and help make the point"},{"time":557180,"text":"that as we did this inventory,"},{"time":559538,"text":"we needed to be able to look at"},{"time":561131,"text":"massive amounts of information."},{"time":563304,"text":"Our genetic information is organized"},{"time":565591,"text":"into a set of 46 volumes,"},{"time":568478,"text":"and when we did that, we had to be able to account"},{"time":570387,"text":"for each of those 46 volumes,"},{"time":572371,"text":"because in some cases with autism,"},{"time":574224,"text":"there's actually a single volume that's missing."},{"time":576680,"text":"We had to get more granular than that, though,"},{"time":578990,"text":"and so we had to start opening those books,"},{"time":581310,"text":"and in some cases, the genetic change"},{"time":583190,"text":"was more subtle."},{"time":584578,"text":"It might have been a single\nparagraph that was missing,"},{"time":587764,"text":"or yet, even more subtle than that,"},{"time":591042,"text":"a single letter,"},{"time":592734,"text":"one out of three billion letters"},{"time":595536,"text":"that was changed, that was altered,"},{"time":597810,"text":"yet had profound effects"},{"time":599407,"text":"in terms of how the brain functions"},{"time":601320,"text":"and affects behavior."},{"time":603137,"text":"In doing this within these families,"},{"time":605514,"text":"we were able to account for approximately"},{"time":607832,"text":"25 percent of the individuals"},{"time":610157,"text":"and determine that there was a single"},{"time":612704,"text":"powerful genetic factor"},{"time":614900,"text":"that caused autism within those families."},{"time":618024,"text":"On the other hand, there's 75 percent"},{"time":620276,"text":"that we still haven't figured out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622727,"text":"As we did this, though,"},{"time":624197,"text":"it was really quite humbling,"},{"time":626291,"text":"because we realized that there was not simply"},{"time":628656,"text":"one gene for autism."},{"time":630597,"text":"In fact, the current estimates are"},{"time":632346,"text":"that there are 200 to 400 different genes"},{"time":635098,"text":"that can cause autism."},{"time":636990,"text":"And that explains, in part,"},{"time":638359,"text":"why we see such a broad spectrum"},{"time":640476,"text":"in terms of its effects."},{"time":642519,"text":"Although there are that many genes,"},{"time":644744,"text":"there is some method to the madness."},{"time":647092,"text":"It's not simply random"},{"time":649040,"text":"200, 400 different genes,"},{"time":651270,"text":"but in fact they fit together."},{"time":653064,"text":"They fit together in a pathway."},{"time":654930,"text":"They fit together in a network"},{"time":656402,"text":"that's starting to make sense now"},{"time":658234,"text":"in terms of how the brain functions."},{"time":660932,"text":"We're starting to have a bottom-up approach"},{"time":663078,"text":"where we're identifying those genes,"},{"time":664787,"text":"those proteins, those molecules,"},{"time":667265,"text":"understanding how they interact together"},{"time":669175,"text":"to make that neuron work,"},{"time":670572,"text":"understanding how those neurons interact together"},{"time":673309,"text":"to make circuits work,"},{"time":674528,"text":"and understand how those circuits work"},{"time":676544,"text":"to now control behavior,"},{"time":678370,"text":"and understand that both in individuals with autism"},{"time":681170,"text":"as well as individuals who have normal cognition."},{"time":685071,"text":"But early diagnosis is a key for us."},{"time":687529,"text":"Being able to make that diagnosis"},{"time":689488,"text":"of someone who's susceptible"},{"time":690995,"text":"at a time in a window"},{"time":693050,"text":"where we have the ability to transform,"},{"time":695397,"text":"to be able to impact"},{"time":697000,"text":"that growing, developing brain is critical."},{"time":699740,"text":"And so folks like Ami Klin have developed methods"},{"time":703549,"text":"to be able to take infants, small babies,"},{"time":706117,"text":"and be able to use biomarkers,"},{"time":708650,"text":"in this case eye contact and eye tracking,"},{"time":711988,"text":"to identify an infant at risk."},{"time":714074,"text":"This particular infant, you can see,"},{"time":716239,"text":"making very good eye contact with this woman"},{"time":718440,"text":"as she's singing \"Itsy, Bitsy Spider,\""},{"time":720800,"text":"in fact is not going to develop autism."},{"time":723840,"text":"This baby we know is going to be in the clear."},{"time":726720,"text":"On the other hand, this other baby"},{"time":729080,"text":"is going to go on to develop autism."},{"time":731415,"text":"In this particular child, you can see,"},{"time":733642,"text":"it's not making good eye contact."},{"time":735843,"text":"Instead of the eyes focusing in"},{"time":737810,"text":"and having that social connection,"},{"time":740088,"text":"looking at the mouth, looking at the nose,"},{"time":742726,"text":"looking off in another direction,"},{"time":744509,"text":"but not again socially connecting,"},{"time":747422,"text":"and being able to do this on a very large scale,"},{"time":750135,"text":"screen infants, screen children for autism,"},{"time":753135,"text":"through something very robust, very reliable,"},{"time":756059,"text":"is going to be very helpful to us in terms of being"},{"time":758775,"text":"able to intervene at an early stage"},{"time":760869,"text":"when we can have the greatest impact."}]},{"cues":[{"time":764301,"text":"How are we going to intervene?"},{"time":766547,"text":"It's probably going to be a combination of factors."},{"time":769377,"text":"In part, in some individuals,"},{"time":771416,"text":"we're going to try and use medications."},{"time":773295,"text":"And so in fact, identifying the genes for autism"},{"time":776017,"text":"is important for us"},{"time":777543,"text":"to identify drug targets,"},{"time":779409,"text":"to identify things that we might be able to impact"},{"time":782032,"text":"and can be certain that that's really"},{"time":783730,"text":"what we need to do in autism."},{"time":785425,"text":"But that's not going to be the only answer."},{"time":788166,"text":"Beyond just drugs, we're going\nto use educational strategies."},{"time":791676,"text":"Individuals with autism,"},{"time":792951,"text":"some of them are wired a little bit differently."},{"time":795248,"text":"They learn in a different way."},{"time":797107,"text":"They absorb their surroundings in a different way,"},{"time":799441,"text":"and we need to be able to educate them"},{"time":801660,"text":"in a way that serves them best."},{"time":804753,"text":"Beyond that, there are a lot of individuals"},{"time":806671,"text":"in this room who have great ideas"},{"time":808817,"text":"in terms of new technologies we can use,"},{"time":811361,"text":"everything from devices we can use to train the brain"},{"time":814480,"text":"to be able to make it more efficient"},{"time":816029,"text":"and to compensate for areas in which"},{"time":817702,"text":"it has a little bit of trouble,"},{"time":819296,"text":"to even things like Google Glass."},{"time":821575,"text":"You could imagine, for instance, Gabriel,"},{"time":823359,"text":"with his social awkwardness,"},{"time":825180,"text":"might be able to wear Google Glass"},{"time":826638,"text":"with an earpiece in his ear,"},{"time":828169,"text":"and have a coach be able to help him,"},{"time":830096,"text":"be able to help think about conversations,"},{"time":832754,"text":"conversation-starters,"},{"time":834070,"text":"being able to even perhaps one day"},{"time":836181,"text":"invite a girl out on a date."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838549,"text":"All of these new technologies"},{"time":840761,"text":"just offer tremendous opportunities"},{"time":842767,"text":"for us to be able to impact"},{"time":844672,"text":"the individuals with autism,"},{"time":847357,"text":"but yet we have a long way to go."},{"time":849893,"text":"As much as we know,"},{"time":851203,"text":"there is so much more that we don't know,"},{"time":854160,"text":"and so I invite all of you"},{"time":856293,"text":"to be able to help us think about"},{"time":858535,"text":"how to do this better,"},{"time":859946,"text":"to use as a community our collective wisdom"},{"time":862825,"text":"to be able to make a difference,"},{"time":864631,"text":"and in particular,"},{"time":865888,"text":"for the individuals in families with autism,"},{"time":868592,"text":"I invite you to join the interactive autism network,"},{"time":871847,"text":"to be part of the solution to this,"},{"time":874041,"text":"because it's going to take really a lot of us"},{"time":876920,"text":"to think about what's important,"},{"time":879190,"text":"what's going to be a meaningful difference."},{"time":881115,"text":"As we think about something"},{"time":882620,"text":"that's potentially a solution,"},{"time":884452,"text":"how well does it work?"},{"time":886111,"text":"Is it something that's really\ngoing to make a difference"},{"time":888059,"text":"in your lives, as an individual,"},{"time":890428,"text":"as a family with autism?"},{"time":892081,"text":"We're going to need individuals of all ages,"},{"time":894501,"text":"from the young to the old,"},{"time":896228,"text":"and with all different shapes and sizes"},{"time":898387,"text":"of the autism spectrum disorder"},{"time":900224,"text":"to make sure that we can have an impact."},{"time":902400,"text":"So I invite all of you to join the mission"},{"time":904605,"text":"and to help to be able to make the lives"},{"time":907579,"text":"of individuals with autism"},{"time":909265,"text":"so much better and so much richer."},{"time":911196,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":913921,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}